      "name": "Flow field velocity comparison against FDA PIV benchmark data",
      "description": "CFD velocity magnitude compared against particle image velocimetry measurements at 3 operating points. Mean absolute error 8.4% across measurement planes; turbulent kinetic energy underpredicted by 22% in impeller wake regions.",
      "outcome": "Partial agreement — velocity profiles within acceptable bounds; turbulence model deficiencies identified in high-shear zones relevant to hemolysis."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-index-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index prediction vs. in-vitro measurements",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed operating points. CFD predictions fall within factor of 2.1 of measured values; systematic underprediction observed at high rotational speeds.",
      "outcome": "Insufficient — absolute hemolysis threshold cannot be confirmed within required uncertainty bounds at MRL 5."
    },
    {
